==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*guma-'', from Indo-European ''*g'həmo-, g'homo-''. Germanic cognates include Old Saxon [[gumo]], Old High German [[gumo]], Old Norse [[gumi]] (Norwegian [[gume]]), Gothic [[𐌲𐌿𐌼𐌰]]. The IE root is also the source of Latin [[homo]], Baltic ''*žmo-'' (Lithuanian [[žmogus|žmōgùs]]).

